{
  "title": "Events and Gestures",
  "subtitle": "Event flow, listeners, gesture recognizers, timers, keyboard handling, and drag-and-drop.",
  "content": [
    {
      "type": "ContentText",
      "body": "<p>STRVCT provides two layers for handling user interaction: <strong>event listeners</strong> that wrap native DOM events and forward them to handler methods on views, and <strong>gesture recognizers</strong> that interpret sequences of events as higher-level gestures like taps, pans, and pinches. A managed <strong>timer system</strong> supports deferred work with both strong and GC-friendly weak timeouts.</p><p>Most application code uses gesture recognizers rather than raw event listeners. The gesture system unifies mouse and touch input, handles multi-touch emulation on desktop, and coordinates competing gestures through a global <code>SvGestureManager</code>.</p>\n<svg viewBox=\"0 0 820 460\" width=\"820\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\">\n  <style>\n    text { font-family: 'Inter', system-ui, -apple-system, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; fill: #111; }\n    .b { font-weight: 600; }\n    .dim { fill: #666; }\n    .box { fill: none; stroke: #111; stroke-width: 1; }\n    .fill { fill: #f0ede5; stroke: #111; stroke-width: 1; }\n    .flow { stroke: #111; stroke-width: 1; fill: none; }\n  </style>\n  <defs>\n    <marker id=\"aeg\" viewBox=\"0 0 10 10\" refX=\"9\" refY=\"5\" markerWidth=\"7\" markerHeight=\"7\" orient=\"auto\">\n      <path d=\"M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z\" fill=\"#111\"/>\n    </marker>\n  </defs>\n  <rect class=\"fill\" x=\"220\" y=\"20\" width=\"380\" height=\"52\"/>\n  <text x=\"235\" y=\"40\" class=\"b\">Browser DOM Event</text>\n  <text x=\"235\" y=\"58\" class=\"dim\">mousedown, touchstart, keydown, drop, ...</text>\n  <line class=\"flow\" x1=\"410\" y1=\"72\" x2=\"410\" y2=\"115\" marker-end=\"url(#aeg)\"/>\n  <rect class=\"fill\" x=\"220\" y=\"115\" width=\"380\" height=\"70\"/>\n  <text x=\"235\" y=\"135\" class=\"b\">SvEventListener</text>\n  <text x=\"235\" y=\"153\" class=\"dim\">wraps a DOM event; calls a named method</text>\n  <text x=\"235\" y=\"171\" class=\"dim\">on the delegate view (e.g. onMouseDown)</text>\n  <line class=\"flow\" x1=\"410\" y1=\"185\" x2=\"410\" y2=\"225\" marker-end=\"url(#aeg)\"/>\n  <text x=\"425\" y=\"212\" class=\"dim\">if a gesture recognizer is attached</text>\n  <rect class=\"box\" x=\"220\" y=\"225\" width=\"380\" height=\"96\"/>\n  <text x=\"235\" y=\"249\" class=\"b\">SvGestureRecognizer  \u00b7  optional layer</text>\n  <text x=\"235\" y=\"267\" class=\"dim\">state machine consumes raw events;</text>\n  <text x=\"235\" y=\"285\" class=\"dim\">SvGestureManager arbitrates competing gestures;</text>\n  <text x=\"235\" y=\"303\" class=\"dim\">sends onGestureBegin / Move / Complete to view</text>\n  <line class=\"flow\" x1=\"410\" y1=\"321\" x2=\"410\" y2=\"365\" marker-end=\"url(#aeg)\"/>\n  <rect class=\"fill\" x=\"220\" y=\"365\" width=\"380\" height=\"52\"/>\n  <text x=\"235\" y=\"385\" class=\"b\">View Handler</text>\n  <text x=\"235\" y=\"403\" class=\"dim\">application logic runs</text>\n  <text x=\"410\" y=\"450\" text-anchor=\"middle\" class=\"dim\">For raw events without gestures, the listener calls the view's handler method directly, skipping the gesture layer.</text>\n</svg>"
    },
    {
      "type": "ContentCards",
